Xethux is right on point. We have a legislative branch for a reason. These people are elected by you and I to control the pursestrings of our hard earned taxes. Reagan/North and that cabal knew damn well that if they had openly approached the American people with the proposition of ' Hey Joe Taxpayer, can you lend us the money to prop up a paramilitary force to overthrow the ELECTED government of Nicuragua' we would have collectively told them to get bent. Instead they opted to smuggle drugs into our country ( now now Nancy... just say NO ) to purchase weapons for the Mullahs in Iran... yeah, that woulda gone over well with the American people. They were caught and they all denied knowing anything ( poindexter was a terrible actor, Ronald on the other hand....hmm, he was so befuddled you 'almost' believed ). Ironic isn't it that they renamed Washington Natl. airport after the guy who threw all the air-traffic controllers out on their asses ).<br>
<br>
P.S. Samm Walton is only a hero to those with no understanding of the economic impact that syphoning away mass amounts of money from a local economy and replacing it with low paying non-union jobs has. The better communities ( at least here out west ) have no Wal-Marts.<br>
